comment_data.body:
Looks like the cache might have to be cleared see:

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/53505896/all-activities-and-layouts-got-corrupted-in-android-studio
Please let us know if clearing the cache fixes the issue.
As I remember "clear caches and restart" doesn't work but i'll try do do it once again after this bug occurred again (5th time right now)

MacOS:
Go to: /Users/userName/Library/Preferences/AndroidStudio3.4/options
Find "runner.layout.xml"
Change the name of this file for ex: runner01.layout.xml
Restart Android studio

Done

Can't think of anything we should add to the flutter intellij plugin to fix this issue. If there is a general Android Studio feature that you think should be added to make this case work better please go ahead and file it at.
https://developer.android.com/studio/report-bugs

Hi there! 

So I don't know where the issue is, but you can minimize the console output in the run tab by clicking this small arrow on the console tab name: ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4112256/63023034-76e2cd80-bea4-11e9-8cc6-16a5a33937d2.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4112256/63023059-86621680-bea4-11e9-8b6a-c364f4578d4a.png)

But after you click it there is now way to restore it! 

You will have to restore `~/Library/Preferences/AndroidStudio3.4/options/runner.layout.xml` (macOS but same should apply for other OS) this lines:

```
       <ViewImpl>
         <option name="ID" value="ConsoleContent" />
         <option name="minimizedInGrid" value="false" />
         <option name="placeInGrid" value="bottom" />
         <option name="tabIndex" value="-1" />
         <option name="window" value="0" />
       </ViewImpl>
```

Replace 
```
<option name="minimizedInGrid" value="true" />
```
by
```
<option name="minimizedInGrid" value="false" />
```

And it's back again!
